data.description: Principles and applications of chemical equilibrium, electrochemistry, thermodynamics, kinetics, organic chemistry and other topics that may include nuclear chemistry, biological chemistry and coordination chemistry. Equivalent to lecture-only part ofCHEM 104. Provides a mechanism for awarding credit for experiences with no laboratory component. The combination ofCHEM 102andCHEM 106is equivalent toCHEM 104.
data.title: GENERAL CHEMISTRY II
